  sodium: 290 mg
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all
produce. Dice @sweet potato{1} into ½-inch pieces. Halve, peel, and slice
@red onion{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2},
separating whites from greens. Dice @roma tomato{1}. Zest and quarter
@lime{1}.

Toss sweet potato on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of
@vegetable oil{}, @salt{}, @pepper{}, and @southwest spice blend{½%tbsp}. Toss
onion on opposite side with @vegetable oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on
top rack, tossing halfway through, until browned and tender,
~{25%minutes}.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add
scallion whites and cook until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add @jasmine rice{½%cup},
¾ cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a large pinch of @salt{}. Bring to
a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until tender,
~{15%minutes}. Keep covered until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{4%tbsp}, juice from 1 lime
wedge, and a pinch of @chipotle powder{1%tsp} (start with ¼ tsp and add more to
taste). Stir in water, 1 tsp at a time, until mixture reaches a drizzling
consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Pat @chicken cutlets{2%10oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season with @salt{},
@pepper{}, and remaining southwest spice. Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{}
in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned
and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #cutting board{}.
Let rest ~{2%minutes}, then slice crosswise.

In a second small bowl, combine tomato, scallion greens, juice from 1 lime
wedge, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in
@butter{1%tbsp}, lime zest (to taste), juice from 1 lime wedge, @salt{}, and
@pepper{}. Divide rice between #bowls{}. Top with veggies, chicken, and salsa.
Drizzle with chipotle crema. Serve with remaining lime wedge on the side.

> Add remaining @southwest spice blend{½%tbsp} to chicken seasoning if using
> entire tablespoon from the original recipe (½ tbsp for potato, ½ tbsp for
> chicken).